---
import KilocodeLayout from "../../layouts/KilocodeLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/tips-shared.css";
---

<KilocodeLayout
  title="Kilo Code Tips & Tricks — Power User Guide"
  description="Selection context, task history, MCP tools, auto-approve patterns, token budget management, and concurrent tasks."
  currentPage="tips"
>
  <div class="tips-wrapper">

    <header class="tips-hero">
      <span class="tips-hero__eyebrow">Kilo Code · Power User</span>
      <h1 class="tips-hero__title">
        Tips &amp; <span class="tips-hero__accent">Tricks</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="tips-hero__desc">Selection-as-context, persistent task history, MCP tool setup, auto-approve patterns, token budget awareness, and concurrent task workflows.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="tips-section">
      <div class="tips-section__header">
        <span class="tips-section__icon">⚡</span>
        <h2 class="tips-section__title">Quick Wins</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tips-cards">

        <div class="tips-card tips-card--highlight">
          <span class="tips-card__num">01</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">Select first, then ask</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">Always select the relevant code before starting a task. That selection becomes your context anchor — Kilo Code focuses on it and its surrounding context, not the whole project at once.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-card">
          <span class="tips-card__num">02</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">Task history is persistent</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">Kilo Code saves all your tasks. Reopen old tasks to continue work, reference what you did, or see what decisions were made. Never lose a conversation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-card">
          <span class="tips-card__num">03</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">Watch the token budget indicator</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">When the token budget indicator gets low, start a new task rather than continuing. Trying to push through causes degraded output quality as context gets compressed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-card">
          <span class="tips-card__num">04</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">MCP tools multiply your capability</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">Set up MCP tools for your stack — database queries, API calls, test runners — before starting big tasks. They let Kilo Code take real actions, not just suggest them.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-card">
          <span class="tips-card__num">05</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">Concurrent tasks for parallel work</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">Kilo Code supports multiple concurrent tasks. Run a refactor in one task while asking questions about docs in another. They don't interfere.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-card">
          <span class="tips-card__num">06</span>
          <div class="tips-card__title">Checkpoint before risky ops</div>
          <p class="tips-card__desc">Before any large edit or refactor, save a checkpoint. You can revert to it cleanly if the output isn't what you wanted — no manual undo chains.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tips-section">
      <div class="tips-section__header">
        <span class="tips-section__icon">🔍</span>
        <h2 class="tips-section__title">Hidden Features</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tips-features">

        <div class="tips-feature">
          <span class="tips-feature__icon">🎯</span>
          <div class="tips-feature__body">
            <div class="tips-feature__title">Restrict auto-approve to specific patterns</div>
            <p class="tips-feature__desc">Auto-approve doesn't have to be all-or-nothing. Configure it in Kilo Code settings to only auto-approve for specific file types or directories (e.g., only test files, only src/, never config/). More safety, less friction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-feature">
          <span class="tips-feature__icon">📚</span>
          <div class="tips-feature__body">
            <div class="tips-feature__title">Kilo reads VS Code workspace settings</div>
            <p class="tips-feature__desc">Your VS Code workspace settings (.vscode/settings.json) add context about your project — linting rules, formatter settings, language versions. Kilo Code picks this up automatically and respects your configured toolchain.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-feature">
          <span class="tips-feature__icon">🔌</span>
          <div class="tips-feature__body">
            <div class="tips-feature__title">MCP tools work with any local or remote server</div>
            <p class="tips-feature__desc">MCP (Model Context Protocol) tools can connect to local CLI tools, databases, REST APIs, or any MCP-compatible server. You're not limited to built-in integrations — wire up your own internal APIs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-feature">
          <span class="tips-feature__icon">⏪</span>
          <div class="tips-feature__body">
            <div class="tips-feature__title">Checkpoint saves are reversible, always</div>
            <p class="tips-feature__desc">A checkpoint before a large edit means you can always get back to a clean state — even if Kilo makes 50 file changes. Much more reliable than trying to manually undo a complex refactor.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tips-section">
      <div class="tips-section__header">
        <span class="tips-section__icon">💀</span>
        <h2 class="tips-section__title">Common Mistakes</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tips-gotchas">

        <div class="tips-gotcha">
          <span class="tips-gotcha__skull">☠️</span>
          <div class="tips-gotcha__title">Starting tasks without selecting code</div>
          <p class="tips-gotcha__desc">Without a selection, Kilo Code has to guess what you're working on. Results are broader and less precise. Your selection is the signal — don't leave it out.</p>
          <span class="tips-gotcha__fix">Always select the relevant code before triggering a task. Makes every interaction more targeted.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-gotcha">
          <span class="tips-gotcha__skull">☠️</span>
          <div class="tips-gotcha__title">Auto-approve on unfamiliar codebases</div>
          <p class="tips-gotcha__desc">Auto-approve is powerful and fast, but it can make sweeping changes to code you haven't fully read yet. On new or inherited codebases, the risk of unintended changes is real.</p>
          <span class="tips-gotcha__fix">Use manual approval on any codebase you haven't fully reviewed. Enable auto-approve only after you understand what you're working with.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-gotcha">
          <span class="tips-gotcha__skull">☠️</span>
          <div class="tips-gotcha__title">Ignoring the token budget until it's empty</div>
          <p class="tips-gotcha__desc">When the context window fills up, Kilo starts compressing earlier parts of the conversation. Quality drops noticeably and you may get contradictory results.</p>
          <span class="tips-gotcha__fix">Start a new task when you see the budget getting low. Fresh context = better output.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-gotcha">
          <span class="tips-gotcha__skull">☠️</span>
          <div class="tips-gotcha__title">Not setting up MCP tools before big tasks</div>
          <p class="tips-gotcha__desc">Without tools, Kilo Code can only read and write files — it can't actually run your tests, query your DB, or call your APIs. You miss out on the full automation loop.</p>
          <span class="tips-gotcha__fix">Set up at least a test runner MCP tool before any significant development work. It transforms suggestions into executable actions.</span>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tips-section">
      <div class="tips-section__header">
        <span class="tips-section__icon">🔄</span>
        <h2 class="tips-section__title">Workflow Combos</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tips-recipes">

        <div class="tips-recipe">
          <div class="tips-recipe__header">
            <span class="tips-recipe__icon">🧪</span>
            <span class="tips-recipe__name">TDD loop — write tests, make them pass</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tips-recipe__body">
            <p class="tips-recipe__desc">Use Kilo Code with a test runner MCP tool for a true red-green-refactor loop without leaving VS Code.</p>
            <div class="tips-recipe__steps">
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">1.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">Select the function you want to test → "Write unit tests for this function"</span></div>
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">2.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">Kilo generates tests and (with MCP test runner) runs them — shows you what passes/fails</span></div>
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">3.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">"Fix the failing tests" — Kilo iterates on the implementation until all pass</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-recipe">
          <div class="tips-recipe__header">
            <span class="tips-recipe__icon">🏃</span>
            <span class="tips-recipe__name">Parallel refactor + review</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tips-recipe__body">
            <p class="tips-recipe__desc">Run a big refactor in one task while asking architecture questions in another. Both run simultaneously.</p>
            <div class="tips-recipe__steps">
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">1.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">Task 1: "Migrate all class components in src/components/ to React hooks" — let it run</span></div>
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">2.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">Task 2 (simultaneously): "Explain the current state management approach and suggest improvements"</span></div>
              <div class="tips-recipe__step"><span class="tips-recipe__step-num">3.</span><span class="tips-recipe__step-text">Review both outputs. Apply the state management insights to guide the next refactor task.</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</KilocodeLayout>
